"{\"uid\": \"velo.outsideonline.com-olympics-elouan-gardon-delivers-first-para-cycling-medal-at-paris-2024-for-team-usa\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Powered byOutside  (Photo: DIMITAR DILKOFF/AFP via Getty Images)  Elouan Gardon (Acme, Washington) powered to bronze forTeam USAfor the first U.S. cycling medal in theParis 2024 Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 51, \"end\": 56, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999127373146267, \"rank\": 4.776134662804917e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 81, \"end\": 97, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acme,_Washington\", \"score\": 0.999999999975671, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Acme, Washington\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acme,_Washington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acme,_Washington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competing in the men's 4000-meter C5 individual pursuit, the 18-year-old narrowly missed gold medal contention, but secured a spot in the bronze medal final.\", \"from\": 199, \"to\": 356, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He roared to bronze six seconds ahead of Austria's Franz-Josef Lasser.\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 428, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"score\": 0.7634692485965666, \"rank\": 0.30948563101108995, \"text\": \"Austria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It feels pretty surreal,\\\" Gardon said in a Team USA release.\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 474, \"end\": 482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9686746058848084, \"rank\": 0.021158455689993704, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am so incredibly happy, and happy to get the first medal for Para-cycling in the Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not wait to continue.\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have never had a crowd like this before,\\\" Gardon said.\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 680, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The feeling is absolutely exciting.\\\"\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 718, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The youngest member of@usparacyclingtakes home BRONZE in his Paralympic debut!Incredible performance from Elouan Gardon!#ParisParalympicspic.twitter.com/dJDaCeBMOI    Veteran teammate Bryan Larsen (Windsor, California) spotted Gardon's talent as a road rider and encouraged him to pursuepara-cycling.\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 1020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 904, \"end\": 909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\", \"score\": 0.8535265909252858, \"rank\": 0.16949806676541046, \"text\": \"Bryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mike_Bryan\"}, {\"begin\": 918, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsor,_California\", \"score\": 0.9999999999947704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Windsor, California\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsor,_California\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsor,_California\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After receiving an invitation to a talent identification camp in June, it became evident that Gardon possessed untapped potential, officials said.\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1168, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Larsen also took to the track, competing in the men's 4000m C4 individual pursuit race opposite Team France, where the rowdy home crowds did not rattle Larsen.\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1266, \"end\": 1277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_France\", \"score\": 0.8336437903501275, \"rank\": 0.19817451264241645, \"text\": \"Team France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A1_Team_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was almost numbing to a certain degree, it was almost better,\\\" Larsen said.\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Because it was so loud, it almost drowned my own thoughts, which sometimes negative thoughts can creep in.\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was really, really happy to be able to subconsciously stick to my habits.\\\"\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Larsen beat his own national record by nearly a full second, a time he had previously set in March at the 2024 UCI Para-Cycling World Championships, but that was not enough to reach the medal round.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1708, \"end\": 1711, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 2.9782191149921067e-12, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Cycliste_Internationale\"}]}]}"